1 [(2)] (II) [the use of the transmission line] will best promote economic and
2 efficient service to the public;
3 (III) WILL BEST MAINTAIN HISTORICAL, ENVIRONMENTAL, OR
4 AGRICULTURAL PRESERVATION AREAS; OR
5 (IV) WILL AVOID ANY OVERLAP WITH A LOT, PARCEL, OR TRACT
6 OF LAND THAT IS:
7 1. LOCATED WITHIN A PLANNED GROWTH AREA
8 IDENTIFIED IN THE LOCAL JURISDICTION’S COMPREHENSIVE PLAN; OR
9 2. ZONED FOR RESIDENTIAL USE OR MIXED USE WITH A
10 RESIDENTIAL COMPONENT.
11 (2) ALTERNATIVES TO THE CONSTRUCTION OF A NEW TRANSMISSION
12 LINE INCLUDE:
13 (I) THE USE OF AN EXISTING TRANSMISSION LINE OF ANOTHER
14 COMPANY;
15 (II) THE USE OF AN EXISTING RIGHT–OF–WAY;
16 (III) RECONDUCTORING AN EXISTING TRANSMISSION LINE; AND
17 (IV) UNDERGROUNDING A TRANSMISSION LINE.
18 (b) In considering the use of an [existing transmission line] ALTERNATIVE under
19 subsection (a) of this section, the Commission need not consider whether the company that
20 owns the line has a franchise in a service area.
21 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
22 October 1, 2025.

